programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E5
programme.desc: In 2011, almost a decade since the release of its last flagship model, the Murcielago, Lamborghini launched its latest creation – the Aventador. Megafactories visits its factory in northern Italy, to follow the story of its creation from conception to launch and to witness an incredible production process.

programme.title: Car SOS S7E7
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz are off to Kent to try and salvage a 1991 VW T4 Campervan. The vehicle belongs to 42 year old carpenter Jon who bought his mobile home several year ago with the dream of taking his wife travelling around the world. Sadly before Jon's dream came true he was diagnosed with brain cancer, his whole world ground to a halt and his plans to restore and drive his beloved van had to go on hold. Will the Car SOS team be able to help resurrect Jon's dream?

programme.title: Machine Impossible E6
programme.desc: Mischa and Max seek out high-tech thrills and spills for amusement! They also rise to a challenge to design and build a technology-inspired sport game, a classic arcade game. It brings the physicality and atmosphere of a soccer match to the virtual world. Will it be a smash hit - or a gaming flop?

programme.title: Rescued E2
programme.desc: In this episode a freak accident severs a professional cyclist's artery miles from medical help, a kayaker fights to rescue his friend who's trapped upside down in white water rapids, and a backcountry skier is buried alive in a tree well.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E1
programme.desc: National Geographic digital nomad Andrew Evans gets under the skin of Eastern Turkey, travelling from the ruined city of Ani to the stone circles of Gobekli Tepe, considered the world's oldest temple. Travelling the same roads that oriental spice and silk traders used for thousands of years he discovers how the many civilisations that passed through the region have left their mark on the food, culture and architecture of modern Turkey.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E3
programme.desc: Follow travel consultant Greer as she heads north to Vancouver, an exciting Canadian city that's blessed with natural sights and urban delights. Local consultant Eppa Lea is her guide as the duo explores Vancouver in 48 hours from top to bottom – literally!

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E4
programme.desc: After touching down in Cape Town, Greer meets up with travel consultant and local Capetonian Janice, who introduces her to the best of the region, from beaches and wineries to wild rhinos and giraffes. It's one amazing experience after another – go Greer!

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E3
programme.desc: Jordan's on the west coast checking out what Vancouver has to offer after hours. His first stop is for a taste of Espana, a tapas bar in English Bay that keeps tradition alive by serving up a Spanish late night menu. Jordan cracks into a Spanish version of a British scotch egg, and follows that up with incredible seafood paella.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E4
programme.desc: When the sun sets on Steeltown, Jordan Andino hits the streets to uncover unexpected late night delights in Pittsburgh. First Jordan heads to The Yard in Shadyside where they are grilling up more than 29 different kinds of grilled cheese! Jordan tries a breakfast grilled cheese that's sure to leave egg on his face.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5 Compilations E4
programme.desc: The bluefin tuna fishery in the Outer Banks offers a big payout. But to reap the reward, the fleet must overcome a never-ending rolodex of hiccups, hurdles, and headaches at sea. Whether it's a mechanical malfunction, bait-snatching birds, or the deadly Oregon Inlet passageway itself, we'll countdown the biggest obstacles that have stood in the way of our captains and their bluefin tuna.

programme.title: China From Above S1E2
programme.desc: Take to the air to see how modern China lives, eats, works, travels and plays on a mega scale. You will learn how this nation has transformed its cities and infrastructure while still retaining its traditions, and how China's industrialization impacts the planet in negative ways while local people are seeking solutions. Also, find out what a billion plus population does for fun.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E8
programme.desc: A turboprop commuter plane is approaching a remote airport in Papua, Indonesia, when it mysteriously disappears. Billowing smoke on a nearby mountaintop leads search-and-rescue teams to the wreckage. And while three separate systems could have prevented the tragedy, it's up to investigators to figure out why none of them did.

programme.desc: An adventure spanning billions of years into the evolution of life and consciousness. A visit to a 100,000-year-old laboratory. The story of the change in life-style that radically altered human existence and the life of the heretic who found god in the book of nature, opening our way to the stars.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E11
programme.sub-title: The Fleeting Grace Of The Habitable Zone
programme.desc: There is no refuge from change in the cosmos. There will come a time in the life of the Sun when Earth will no longer be a home for us. The story of our ancestors who rose to a comparable challenge and a long-term vision of our future on other worlds.

programme.title: Taboo S8E7
programme.desc: Alcohol has played icebreaker at countless parties and Cupid to a plethora of romances, but it is also responsible for addictions, crumbled lives and deaths. From Labor Day weekend parties in Arizona to binge-drinking resorts in Spain, alcohol shapes the lives of those who drink it in ways that can be heart-breaking and deadly.

programme.title: Science Of Stupid S6E8
programme.desc: In this episode we find out the best way to drive a jetski over land, the worst way to ride a bicycle and the dangers of slack lining.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E2
programme.desc: An examination of the techniques and tactics Saddam Hussein used to rise from a low level enforcer to become the supreme leader of Iraq. Through his brutal use of violence, intimidation and torture Saddam Hussein managed to rule the nation for nearly a quarter of a century until he was finally deposed by US forces during the Invasion of Iraq in 2003. Few dictators loom so large in recent history.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E5
programme.desc: Meet China's most affectionate and vocal monkeys in the remote, seasonal forests of Central China. These mountain forests and all who live here, experience unpredictable and harsh weather in a land that can be covered in snow for 4 months of the year. Follow the journey of a baby Golden snub-nosed monkey during the first year of her life as she learns all about her forest home and battles the elements to survive.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E6
programme.desc: A woman's bag is flagged in the x-ray area but she's already been inspected twice. Police must decide whether to tear the bag apart or let her go. An Italian man claims not to understand the police. He may be telling the truth. Or he may be trying to evade the law. A shipment of children's toys may hide a stash of cocaine.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E8
programme.desc: Canadian 21-year-old Christina Jocko is addicted to spending money, partying and taking drugs. But when she discovers opiates her life spirals into addiction. Out of work, out of money and out of luck - an offer of an easy $10,000 for running cocaine from Panama looks like a way out. But little does she realise the tempting adventure will cost her five years of her life.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E1
programme.desc: Can a single meal brighten a child's future? Can a school lunch bridge the gap in education? Let's go back to school with the Akshaya Patra Foundation and learn how the world's largest school lunch program is cooking up millions of meals and offering India's children a hopeful tomorrow, one plate at a time.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E13
programme.desc: After spending some time in the crazy crowds of Old Delhi, David decides to head for the greener pastures of ITC Grand Bharat, a golf resort and a peaceful oasis just outside the city. There, he plays a few holes with the help of a pro and a knowledgeable caddie, and cooks up a storm on the outdoor grill with resident Chef Shiveet.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E1
programme.desc: Like the carnival festivals of Rio and Venice, Goa marks the days before Lent with an all-out celebration: three full days of eating, drinking, and partying. David takes part in all of the festivities, including an appearance on a float in Panjim's annual Carnival kick-off parade. He ends up spending time with some Italian expats and celebrating the holiday Venetian-style.

programme.title: Tut's Treasures: The Last Pharaoh
programme.desc: The discovery of Tutankhamun's tomb in 1922 made headlines across the world sparking a global frenzy for Ancient Egypt. Crammed inside were over priceless artifacts of every type - from gold slippers to finely tooled daggers, the remains of chariots and the boy king's show-stopping solid gold death mask. But of all the 5,398 treasures from the tomb of Tutankhamun it's the ones that paint a picture of Tutankhamun's family that are the most unsettling. Particularly intriguing are two tiny mummified babies found in the tomb. Now being re-examined in the labs of the Grand Egyptian Museum, they give a chilling insight into the bizarre practices that kept the Pharaoh's dynasty in power and ultimately lead to its downfall. DNA analysis reveals the tiny fetuses are Tutankhamun's still born children - the offspring of an incestuous relationship between Tutankhamun and his sister. Similarly DNA evidence suggests Tutankhamun was also the result of incest whilst artifacts, hidden for yea.

programme.title: Egypt With The World's Greatest Explorer E2
programme.desc: On the second leg of their journey, Ran and Joe spend a night inside the only surviving Wonder of the Ancient world - the Great Pyramid of Giza. On their way to Luxor their cross the 'no man's land', where few tourists venture? Much like Ran in 1969, they have a ferry to catch across the Nile. In Luxor they learn the ancient martial art called Tahtib. On their way south Ran has another test for Joe - a race across the Eastern Desert to the Red Sea.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E2
programme.desc: There are only a few days left of deer hunting season in the Blue Ridge Mountains of North Carolina, and homesteaders Tony and Amelia need meat to get them through the cold winter. But Tony has never been deer hunting before and doesn't have the luxury of time to hone his methods. Tony is thrown right in to the hunt, and the pressure is on.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5 Compilations E5
programme.desc: Worlds collide when the Northern boats from Gloucester, MA descend on Outer Banks, NC in a fishing show down. Some of the best fishermen from Gloucester head south for the winter for a shot at the oceans most lucrative prey, bluefin tuna. When they arrive in Southern waters they quickly learn Southern hospitality is dead. The local boys let them Yankees know they are not welcome. All this tension leads to fierce rivalries with explosive results.

programme.title: Mega Air E5
programme.desc: Mega Air gets privileged access to the world's biggest air package handling facility at UPS Worldport, that ingeniously sorts up to 2 million items per night for worldwide delivery. We hitch a ride on the red-eye mail plane shuttle providing a vital service to the Channel Islands. Britain's busiest pure cargo airport is in full fire drill as fireman tackle a mock air freighter inferno and at Helsinki airport mystery freight provides a shocking outcome.

programme.title: Superstructures: Engineering Marvels E6
programme.desc: Germany's Wolfsburg car factory is the largest in the world. This episode uncovers the engineering and production innovations hidden inside it.

programme.title: Taboo S8E4
programme.desc: In every society there are unwritten rules of behavior, codes of conduct that allow people to coexist. When individuals break this code, they may find themselves shunned. In England, a father with Tourette's syndrome finds himself an outcast. In Idaho, a young woman is stigmatized by self-harm. In the UK, a man with narcolepsy is judged to be lazy. In Vermont, 2 friends are thought to be strange.

programme.desc: On this adventure, Greer is going to the city that never sleeps – New York. She'll meet Brooklyn-born-and-raised travel consultant Jessie, who has planned an exciting itinerary to show off her hometown. After these 48 hours, she'll need a good rest!

programme.desc: Gordon has filmed lions in Africa for years and is fully aware that lions don't normally eat people. But some parts of East Africa have been plagued by repeated outbreaks of man-eating-lions and Gordon wants to know the reasons behind it. He travels to Tanzania, where lions have attacked over 1000 people in the past 20 years, to learn what draw the lions in to track and hunt people.

But make no mistake, this is no Eden - from Jaguars to Gibbons, Hummingbirds to Orangutans, meet the incredible animals to discover why their struggles for survival in this crowded and competitive world have never been tougher. As jungle seasons become more unpredictable only the toughest animals will triumph.

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E7
programme.desc: Afzal Kahn gives his team a project that could be their toughest challenge to date - to create a Jeep that is bigger and better than any other. They also have to make it a success in the USA, where the Jeep is held in very high esteem. The job must also be completed in time for the new Jeep to launch in a Hollywood showroom that Khan has specially booked for the occasion.

programme.title: Car SOS S7E8
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz are off to Derbyshire to rescue a 48 year old Italian supercar: a 1971 Lamborghini Espada. This remarkable car belongs to lifelong petrol head Ged who bought the car in 1977 for #4000 however when it eventually broke down Ged's aim of one day restoring it to its former glory ground to a halt when serious health issues got in the way. Will the boys from Car SOS be able to make Ged's dream come true?

programme.title: Egypt With The World's Greatest Explorer E3
programme.desc: After weeks of adventure Ran and Joe have finally reached the end of their journey, to the south is the border with Sudan. In this episode, Joe skirts the crocodile infested waters of Lake Nasser and tries his hand at sailing a traditional Egyptian Felucca. Finally, Ran and Joe say goodbye to this incredible country and its lifeblood, the River Nile, just as Ran did half a century before.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E1
programme.desc: MIA CBP target a passenger with frequent trips to Colombia and after further questioning they suspect he could be smuggling narcotics internally. Officers search cargo for narcotics staying one step ahead of the cartel. At JFK, HSI conducts a controlled delivery of ecstasy on Wall Street that was intercepted at the mail facility and at LAX two passengers are questioned about their visits. For one their past drug use comes back to haunt them.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E5
programme.desc: Indonesia's majestic Joglo vernacular houses are not just architectural displays but also social documents of life in the past. The colonial Dutch history in Indonesia also comes alive through the Old Indies Dutch Style houses.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E6
programme.desc: In this episode we survey the houses of Kotagede and Bandung in Indonesia. There are 2 different styles emerge: the New Indies Dutch and the Eclectic houses. Both are visually striking and show a wealth of architectural designs.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S1E5
programme.desc: FISH OF THE DAY host Clarke Gayford is headed to Rarotonga in search of his target species the Wahoo. Situated between Tahiti and Tonga, Rarotonga is an extinct volcano rising 4000m out of the sea. It's an Island oasis acting as a natural fish attractant for big pelagic species and it's especially reknowned for the fastest striking fish in the ocean - big pelagic Wahoo. Here Clarke sets about attempting to catch one on Rod and Reel before getting into the blue tropical water to see if he can get one on Spear as well. Along the way we meet plenty of friendly locals including a lady who has dedicated her entire life to studying the Humpbacks that visit each year. They also meet a local chef with a 'Pan Fried Wahoo with Prawn & Chilli Salsa and Vanilla Coconut Sauce' dish, he's really keen to show us how to make. Delicious.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S1E6
programme.desc: FISH OF THE DAY host Clarke Gayford is heading inland to target Rainbow Trout on fly. On the way he's got a couple of stops to make, firstly to enter an catfish spearfishing competition and then to try his hand at prawn fishing. Now normally Clarke would catch his target species on rod and reel before attempting to spear one, but you're not allowed to spear trout so he's chasing the invasive Catfish instead. Clarke also meets up with Prawn Farmer Richard Klein to see how he's turned his farm into a tourist attraction and every prawn into a valuable assett. Then it's time to team up with trout guide Louie the Fish and head out in search of Rainbow Trout for the chef at the Chateau Tongariro to cook for a silver dinner service fitting of such a regal species.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S1E7
programme.desc: FISH OF THE DAY host Clarke Gayford is heading to the north of New Zealand and the Bay of Islands. It's an area made famous by American Western Writer Zane Grey in the 1920s and 30s. Grey came here to fish for Marlin and fell in love with the area's unbelievable fishing. Today Clarke is on the hunt for the iconic New Zealand Snapper, one of the best eating fish there is, but he's not just going to catch it on rod and reel, he is also teaming up with Paihia Dive's Craig Johnston and Stu Hofstetter to head out and spear a few too. Before he does though, he's stopping in Deep Water Cove to dive on the wreck of the HMNZS Canterbury - a New Zealand Naval Frigate sunk in 2007 to create an artificial reef.

programme.title: Route Awakening S1E6
programme.desc: The journey winds through the cradle of Chinese civilization in Shanxi and Shandong. Harry meets a bamboo lantern maker, whose craft is considered one of the intangible cultural heritages of China. He also discovers a kind of ancient housing where people lived in silo caves. As he makes his way to Shandong, Harry helps fishermen to catch and sell shrimp, followed by making giant kites in Weifang.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E1
programme.desc: First stop, Xi'an, the starting point of the ancient silk road network and the national food capital of China. With its reputation as one of China's holy grail for foodies, Jamie can't wait to get stuck in to all the exotic flavours from China's central plains and western regions! His taste buds are in for a treat! As well as learning the best amazing dishes this ancient charming city has inherited for thousands of years, he will be knocking up a feast for the new rocker friends and jamming with a rock band!

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E2
programme.desc: Next up on Jamie's silk road food trek, he will travel to Heyang that is well known for being home to some of China's most ancient cooking techniques. He will meet the best local chefs to find out about the oldest Chinese recipes, have a lesson in the art of “bun flower” making and get his hands dirty in the fields in search of the finest ingredients. To top it all off, love is in the air as he experiences a once in a lifetime countryside wedding!

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E6
programme.desc: Down on the sunny coast of Cornwall, world-class, adaptive surfer Peg Leg, wants to do a very unique extension – to his VW campervan home. Peg lives in his van full time and has travelled everywhere from the Arctic Circle to the Sahara desert in search of the best waves on the planet. Despite having no technical training he's hoping to transform his home on wheels by building a new cabin from scratch, for him and his 5 year old daughter, Bluebell.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E5
programme.desc: Indonesia's majestic Joglo vernacular houses are not just architectural displays but also social documents of life in the past. The colonial Dutch history in Indonesia also comes alive through the Old Indies Dutch Style houses.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E6
programme.desc: In this episode we survey the houses of Kotagede and Bandung in Indonesia. There are 2 different styles emerge: the New Indies Dutch and the Eclectic houses. Both are visually striking and show a wealth of architectural designs.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E1
programme.desc: The magnificent temples of Angkor were mysteriously abandoned for hundreds of years. Now, the largest religious monument on Earth is at risk of being lost again. It will take a team effort to restore this legendary world heritage site to its former glory. Researchers are discovering new clues about what went wrong in the past, while locals are fighting to save their heritage for the future.

programme.title: Dive Detectives E5
programme.desc: The Dive Detectives brave pirate and shark infested waters to try and locate the missing subs of WWII and find out why they sunk.

programme.title: Tom's Istanbul Delight E1
programme.desc: Tom is taken on a tour by his Head Chef Deniz to see the ancient sights of the city and sample traditional Turkish cuisine cooked with time-honed methods. Tom wants to learn about the ingredients that make up the cultural recipe of the city, and experience all the tastes, flavors and traditions, then incorporate them into his menu for his new restaurant in Istanbul.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E14
programme.desc: Pablo explores more about Tiwas of Tharakunchi after learning that they are divided into two: The Tiwas of the Hills and Tiwas of the Plains. While he gets a chance to be among the Tiwas during the festivities Pablo is just blown away as he gets to know more about their food, cooking techniques, and their societal views.

programme.title: Pizza In Parma E1
programme.desc: The boys prepare for their big trip to Parma by visiting the best pizzeria in Cardiff, and then cook their own pizzas for a Mariachi band on their last night before setting off in Smokey Pete.

programme.title: Pizza In Parma E2
programme.desc: The boys' first stop is the glorious south west of England, where they learn more about cheese and sausage before putting Smokey Pete to the test to feed some hungry tourists.

programme.title: Pizza In Parma E3
programme.desc: Smokey Pete finally hits the open roads of mainland Europe, where the boys are treated to a fantastic foodie tour of San Sebastian, have an unforgettable meal at one of the World's most famous restaurants, and finally cook some pizzas for a gastronomic society.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E9
programme.desc: Peter Kuruvita arrives in the Mayan stronghold of the Yucatan Peninsula, major producer of one of the hottest chillies on earth - the Habanero, before heading to the state of Tabasco where chocolate has been consumed for thousands of years.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E11
programme.desc: The Palio del Casale, or Donkey Race, brings thousands of spectators and partiers to the town of Camposano. It's a weekend-long party based around old Italian tradition and light competition between neighboring towns, regions, and even countries. Amidst the music, great food and drink, David learns what it's really like to be a donkey jockey, and represents Canada in the race - with exciting results.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E12
programme.desc: In Naples, soccer isn't just a sport, it's a religion, and their fans are world renowned for their dedication, enthusiasm and creativity. David spends a Sunday with S.S.C. Napoli supporters, taking in the sights, sounds and foods (of course!) at Stadio San Paolo.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E1
programme.desc: Ellis Emmett lives for adventure. Having conquered mountains and rivers in his homeland of New Zealand, his sights are now set on exploring the remote islands of the Pacific you can only get to by boat. The only trouble is, he doesn't know how to sail. Ellis struggles with the physical and mental challenges of sailing but with help from friends both old and new, he finds his sea legs and sets off on his quest.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E3
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchens revisit the cold city of their youth, Harbin. Despite its communist roots, Harbin has become a vibrant commercial city that has come to embrace its icy heritage. The brothers swim in icy waters, make an ice sculpture, race down an ice slide, and drink in a bar made of ice, then visit the world famous Harbin Ice Festival.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E7
programme.desc: Plantation pioneers of the 19th century in Malaysia designed homes for comfort and status in the midst of jungles and sprawling farms. From strategic bases close to thriving access points like Penang to rural riverine frontiers in Perak, these quintessential bungalows retain the charm and sense of sanctuary they were first built for.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E8
programme.desc: There is an obvious contrast between the architectural legacy of colonial houses and the Malay vernacular homes built to provide respite from the tropical heat. While the former escaped to the cool hills bringing with them the styles and influences of their motherland, the latter adopted the techniques of time-tested traditional village homes.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E1
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent. It's a journey of a lifetime for the unlikely duo as they traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Meeting with local historian Chen Ban, they trace the footsteps of Hakka pioneers along a series of mountain trails that formed the backbone of their livelihood, transporting commodities and goods. Travelling further south, they get their hands dirty and learn how camphor, one of Taiwan's treasures is traditionally extracted. The duo also learn more about a tea that was created by the Hakka, that embodies the very spirit of what it means to be part of a ethnicity that were once outcasts.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E2
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent, to explore and understand the relationship of Hakka food and their traditional lifestyle. The unlikely duo traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Along the way, Julian and Natalie meet unique characters and learn that the heart of Hakka cuisine stemmed from their traditional way of living.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E3
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison and host-model Natalie Pickles dive head in to Hakka culture by joining a Hakka Opera troupe on stage as they conclude their journey on the Taiwan Romantic Route 3. To get their performance up to scratch, our unlikely duo must first understand the basics of Hakka culture. The pair meet Professor Zheng Rom Shing to understand how Hakka opera's roots began with tea picking, before taking pronunciation lessons with a group of elementary school children. Hakka arts revolves around the environment and community.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E2
programme.desc: Explore two different sides to China's fashion industry. JNBY is the international brand making waves in the fashion scene. In their factories, rolls of fabric are processed on an industrial scale. Hanyi's Master Cheongsam maker has been perfecting his craft for 80 years, and his shop is the oldest on Shanghai's Changle Street. Here, he transforms silk into tailored and embroidered Cheongsam.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E3
programme.desc: Wuzhong, home to the largest Muslim community on the silk road, and of course China's best place to enjoy Chinese halal food. Jamie will learn an unusual breakfast recipe that's certainly not for the faint-hearted and face his hardest noodle challenge yet. He also will uncover the secrets to the healthy yellow riverbank lifestyle that's helped shape the rich culinary history here an also got the younger generation rethinking their diets.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E4
programme.desc: Next stop, Dunhuang, the last city that trade merchants would pass through on the ancient silk road before braving the desert. Jamie will be introduced to the wonders of desert lifestyle to find out how the harsh local terrain has helped to^shape the unique food culture. It will definitely be a crazy ride by spending one day with a caravan of camels and, but all the pay is worth it. Jamie will cook in the VIP desert kitchen and attempt to make the hardest dish to date, for celebrating the unforgettable birthday party.

These world-class thrill seekers search far and wide to find the most epic ride, the steepest climb, the highest jump or the longest flight. Destination Extreme follows these athletes as they discover the ultimate location and explain why that mountain range, ocean swell, or valley floor, can't compare to anywhere else in the world.

programme.title: Destination Extreme E4
programme.desc: Destination Extreme is a Hi Def exploration of the planet's most exciting action sports destinations, told by the athletes that make these hotspots their playground. Destination Extreme follows these athletes as they discover the ultimate location and explain why that mountain range, ocean swell, or valley floor, can't compare to anywhere else in the world.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E3
programme.desc: Bangkok Airport is a friendly place with helpful staff but misunderstandings can still arise as it serves millions of passengers from around the world. There will always be a language barrier as seen with a French mum turned away from her flight, a man losing his juggling sticks, a bossy immigration officer fighting a one-woman war on queue jumping and a French tourist facing deportation.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E13
programme.desc: A trip to Assam is not actually complete without visiting the island of Majuli. On this ever shrinking island Pablo gets to witness the two sides of it. On one hand Pablo meets another prominent tribe of Assam: The Mishing. Houses on stilts, weaving their own clothes, Mishing share their authentic recipe of Apong- the very famous home brewed rice beer with Pablo.

programme.title: A Taste Of South Africa E10
programme.desc: The final episode showcases the many different foods that can be found in South Africa, with origins from all over the world. Matt gets his hands dirty with Ethiopian food in the heart of Johannesburg, Kassa explains his homeland's food and the traditions behind it. After a round of golf, Matt samples Piri Piri and African teas with Burundian chef Coco Reinarhz. Coco shares his grandmother's famous recipe.

programme.title: Ultimate Airport Dubai Compilations S2E4
programme.desc: Public drunkenness is highly offensive in the Middle East, so a pair of highly intoxicated newly-weds in the terminal requires the staff at Dubai Airport to tread cautiously. Care is also needed when loading a 270,000 dollar car on to the hold of a small plane, but Dubai is a millionaires' playground with an expert driver and other wonderful staff who can find more than 70 missing passengers in 15 minutes to save a time-critical departure.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S1E8
programme.desc: FISH OF THE DAY host Clarke Gayford is headed to Fiji to chase Spanish Mackerel in blue water off the Yasawa Islands. But before he does he's stopped in at Pacific Harbour to face one of his biggest fears. He's going to dive with Bull Sharks and he wont be in a cage. From here he heads north-west to Manta Ray Island in the Yasawas where he will attempt to catch a Spanish Mackerel on line and spear one as well. There's even time to take a swim with the Manta Rays. Final day and they are successful is spearing their target for waiting chef Javed and his secret local recipe. But on the way home guide Justin hooks up to the fish of a lifetime - a 40 kilogram GT that drags them and boat dangerously close to the breaking waves as they struggle to stop the screaming reel.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S1E9
programme.desc: FISH OF THE DAY host Clarke Gayford is headed to Wanaka in the South Island of New Zealand to find and catch one of the greatest freshwater challenges there is - the Brown Trout. Now Clarke's no fly fishing guru, so to get a trophy sized brown he's enlisted the help of one of the area's best Guides - Gordy Watson. But before they get underway chef James Stapley asks for a little more than just a Brown Trout to unlock his secret recipe - he wants a sea-run Brown and some crayfish too. Clarke teams up with Oxbow Adventures to fill James' request. His epic journey to catch his Fish of the Day takes him by helicopter across the Southern Alps and out to the wild west coast of Fiordland then back with fish and crayfish in tow for James to serve up a master class in chefing producing one of the dishes of the series.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S1E10
programme.desc: FISH OF THE DAY host Clarke Gayford is headed to one of the most spectacular and isolated island groups in the Pacific - the Solomon Islands. He's on a mission to retrace the footsteps of US President John F Kennedy and the time he here during WWII when his Patrol Torpedo Boat PT-109 was sunk by the Japanese. Clarke's journey takes him north from the capital Honiara to Munda and then on to Gizo as he follows JFKs ill-fated mission and his own mission - to find and catch the elusive Green Jobfish. And he does just off the island where JFK was based, although attempting to spear a Green Jobfish in these almost virgin waters proves far more challenging with the reef systems' alive with sharks.

programme.title: Miguel's Tropical Kitchen E12
programme.desc: Miguel fires up the barbie at the Cairns lagoon, impressing tourists with his Giant King Prawn Skewers. Then it is back to the pool for something totally indulgent, Miguel's classic Chocolate and Almond Cake.

programme.title: Pond Stars E6
programme.desc: The Pond Stars come out of their shell in Atlanta tackling two wild projects in just five days. Their first job is at an environmental center, creating a pond specifically for rescued turtles as an outdoor classroom for an upcoming kids camp. The second project is to build a 35-foot waterfall and 600-gallon reservoir that will have wildlife flocking to this suburban backyard, for the birds.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E7
programme.desc: After touring the outback, Sara arrives in Melbourne and discovers a bar which can only be accessed through a secret door and a cinema overlooking the city's skyscrapers at night. Then, she joins the local community in an annual polo game where city slickers and rural cowboys compete on their riding skills. Finally, she finds out the secret of Michelin-star quality wagyu beef from the stockmen.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E8
programme.desc: Sara drives along the Great Ocean Road and arrives in surf country - Victoria. She discovers a supreme olive oil and reveals the secrets behind the peppery flavor. Surrounded by a vast array of vegetables and fruits, Sara decides to pay tribute to the fresh and natural ingredients by dishing up a salad using indigenous pistachio, local wine and peppery olive oil.

programme.title: Miguel's Tropical Kitchen E13
programme.desc: In this episode of Miguel's Tropical Kitchen our Spanish chef mixes tropical produce with global cuisine, dishing up an exotic Asian beef salad, Italian angel hair pasta with scallops, and a beautiful French Pineapple Tarte Tatin.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E1
programme.desc: Miguel visits one of New Zealand's biggest mussel men and they feast on the traditional fresh seafood cuisine together. Then Miguel rises to the challenge of a dinner party where each guest sets down their own dietary requirement! He decides on cooking Quinoa Raviolo with tomato salsa. Whether it is well-prepared or not, it is the guests' call.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E4
programme.desc: Christopher Columbus. Julia Child. Clarence Birdseye. These are some of the revolutionary men and women who have changed what and how we eat, remaking not just food history but human history. Some of these food revolutionaries are well known, others obscure. But one thing they have in common is that they have fundamentally shaped how we live today.

programme.title: Escape To Costa Rica E1
programme.desc: In this episode Gaia helps capture a rogue crocodile before travelling to the incredible Monteverde Cloud Forest and scaling a giant tree with scientists who preserve the delicate forest life forms. From there she goes to meet the charismatic president of Costa Rica, Luis Guillermo Solis, who explains why Costa Rica puts environmental protection at the top of the national agenda. On the Caribbean coast of the country, Gaia gets up close and personal with the most iconic animal in Costa Rica – the sloth. Finally she travels with the family to celebrate Kip's 4th birthday the on the remote and wild Osa Peninsula.

programme.title: Straight To The Source: Korean Food E1
programme.desc: Before they begin their Korean food tour, Todd and Ricky learn about Korean traditions and sample vegetarian fine-dining in downtown Seoul. Then they head to Cherowan where they visit a farm producing fresh vegetables and try Buddhist temple food. Inspired by their tour experience, they search for ingredients in a supermarket to create their own dish of mushrooms, peppers and shrimp.

programme.title: Straight To The Source: Korean Food E2
programme.desc: Todd and Ricky start their journey in Sunchang where they learn how to make gochujang. Then they are back in Seoul to taste Grilled pork belly, known as Samgyeopsal, with vegetables and ssamjang. Lastly they travel to Andong to learn about doenjang and see how Korean chefs incorporate the sauce into their cooking, and to showcase what they've learnt with their own dish.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E3
programme.desc: The team has been commissioned to revive a showcase aquarium. They must recreate a sea turtle's natural habitat, however, the tank's marine life including sharks and stingrays, cannot be removed from the premises so someone will have to swim with the carnivores. Next, one tough client wants three tanks in one, completed in a fraction of the time the crew allots for such complex projects.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E1
programme.desc: Rob and Leon arrive on the edge of the Gobi Desert and pick up last minute supplies for their 6-month trip.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E2
programme.desc: In Jining, Rob's foot is proven all right by an x-ray. But, not long after that, the pair suffer diarrhea from some ill-prepared food.

Exploring a region rich in seafaring cultures, he immerses himself in the lives of the sailors, sea gypsies, fishermen and marine conservationists who share his passion for life on the open sea.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E3
programme.desc: Explore the waterways of China, home to both sleek, snazzy yachts and lovingly hand-crafted dragon-boats. We uncover the marvels of engineering behind the yachts at Sino-Eagle, and watch master craftsmen painstakingly build traditional dragon-boats.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E4
programme.desc: Relive childhood dreams and delve into the world of traditional and modern toys, from the complex electronic flying RC Helicopters to simple paper kites. See the inner workings of a Syma factory, and then head to the kite capital of the world to learn how art, science and devotion to one's craft brings life to intricate kites.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E5
programme.desc: Explore the changing landscape of music in China, as old and new sounds merge. Deep inside the Pearl River Piano factory, planks of wood are transformed with great precision into intricate instruments, and we see how all the various parts come together. Over at the Shanghai Number 1 Musical Instruments Factory, watch as a master technician guides his apprentices on how to make the perfect Guzheng.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E6
programme.desc: Noodles are a beloved staple of Chinse cuisine, from modern packets of instant noodles to traditional shops selling hand-made noodles. Head into the depths of the Master Kong factory in Tianjin, which produces noodles for the whole country. Then to Sichuan, where Zhongjiang noodles have been handmade since the Song Dynasty.

programme.desc: In this episode of Miguel's Tropical Kitchen our Spanish chef mixes tropical produce with global cuisine, dishing up an exotic Asian beef salad, Italian angel hair pasta with scallops, and a beautiful French Pineapple Tarte Tatin.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E1
programme.desc: Miguel visits one of New Zealand's biggest mussel men and they feast on the traditional fresh seafood cuisine together. Then Miguel rises to the challenge of a dinner party where each guest sets down their own dietary requirement! He decides on cooking Quinoa Raviolo with tomato salsa. Whether it is well-prepared or not, it is the guests' call.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E3
programme.desc: Explore the waterways of China, home to both sleek, snazzy yachts and lovingly hand-crafted dragon-boats. We uncover the marvels of engineering behind the yachts at Sino-Eagle, and watch master craftsmen painstakingly build traditional dragon-boats.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E4
programme.desc: Relive childhood dreams and delve into the world of traditional and modern toys, from the complex electronic flying RC Helicopters to simple paper kites. See the inner workings of a Syma factory, and then head to the kite capital of the world to learn how art, science and devotion to one's craft brings life to intricate kites.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E5
programme.desc: Explore the changing landscape of music in China, as old and new sounds merge. Deep inside the Pearl River Piano factory, planks of wood are transformed with great precision into intricate instruments, and we see how all the various parts come together. Over at the Shanghai Number 1 Musical Instruments Factory, watch as a master technician guides his apprentices on how to make the perfect Guzheng.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E6
programme.desc: Noodles are a beloved staple of Chinse cuisine, from modern packets of instant noodles to traditional shops selling hand-made noodles. Head into the depths of the Master Kong factory in Tianjin, which produces noodles for the whole country. Then to Sichuan, where Zhongjiang noodles have been handmade since the Song Dynasty.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E1
programme.desc: Rob and Leon arrive on the edge of the Gobi Desert and pick up last minute supplies for their 6-month trip.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E2
programme.desc: In Jining, Rob's foot is proven all right by an x-ray. But, not long after that, the pair suffer diarrhea from some ill-prepared food.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E2
programme.desc: The beautiful cathedral of La Sagrada Familia in Barcelona, Spain has been under construction for 130 years, yet it's still not finished. Now, a team of experts is rushing to complete this masterpiece in just thirteen years. To finish this church will take not just innovation and devotion, but the most advanced technology, hard-hat construction, and the fine-grained discipline of ancient craft.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E6
programme.desc: Down on the sunny coast of Cornwall, world-class, adaptive surfer Peg Leg, wants to do a very unique extension – to his VW campervan home. Peg lives in his van full time and has travelled everywhere from the Arctic Circle to the Sahara desert in search of the best waves on the planet. Despite having no technical training he's hoping to transform his home on wheels by building a new cabin from scratch, for him and his 5 year old daughter, Bluebell.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E1
programme.desc: First stop, Xi'an, the starting point of the ancient silk road network and the national food capital of China. With its reputation as one of China's holy grail for foodies, Jamie can't wait to get stuck in to all the exotic flavours from China's central plains and western regions! His taste buds are in for a treat! As well as learning the best amazing dishes this ancient charming city has inherited for thousands of years, he will be knocking up a feast for the new rocker friends and jamming with a rock band!

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E2
programme.desc: Next up on Jamie's silk road food trek, he will travel to Heyang that is well known for being home to some of China's most ancient cooking techniques. He will meet the best local chefs to find out about the oldest Chinese recipes, have a lesson in the art of “bun flower” making and get his hands dirty in the fields in search of the finest ingredients. To top it all off, love is in the air as he experiences a once in a lifetime countryside wedding!

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E4
programme.desc: It is Valentine's Day at the airport. Romance blossoms for immigration officers Bert and Nat, Captain Jack shares the secrets of a successful marriage and there are free hugs for every passenger. Justin jets in for cosmetic surgery to perk up his love life, Nathan introduces his parents to his new Thai boyfriend and a Swiss traveler flies to Thailand to meet his internet girlfriend.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E31
programme.desc: Ben takes us on a virtual taste adventure to Mexico with his fresh chorizo buns, using a range of Mexican spices, along the way he teaches us how salt helps to bind pork mince, and the importance of massaging it to begin a binding process. Ben also explains how cooking meat on a skewer can prevent your meat from being undercooked in the middle.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E32
programme.desc: Ben and the crew travel thorough to the Huon Salmon Parramatta Creek Facility, where Simon explains the process that when the Salmon arrives fresh off the truck at 6am. Ben whips up a quick pickled salad with Huon's Wood Roasted Salmon. Ben and Joel meet at The University of Queensland where they talk through the first ever meal Joel prepared for himself- scrambled eggs.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E14
programme.desc: Pablo explores more about Tiwas of Tharakunchi after learning that they are divided into two: The Tiwas of the Hills and Tiwas of the Plains. While he gets a chance to be among the Tiwas during the festivities Pablo is just blown away as he gets to know more about their food, cooking techniques, and their societal views.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E13
programme.desc: A trip to Assam is not actually complete without visiting the island of Majuli. On this ever shrinking island Pablo gets to witness the two sides of it. On one hand Pablo meets another prominent tribe of Assam: The Mishing. Houses on stilts, weaving their own clothes, Mishing share their authentic recipe of Apong- the very famous home brewed rice beer with Pablo.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E11
programme.desc: The Palio del Casale, or Donkey Race, brings thousands of spectators and partiers to the town of Camposano. It's a weekend-long party based around old Italian tradition and light competition between neighboring towns, regions, and even countries. Amidst the music, great food and drink, David learns what it's really like to be a donkey jockey, and represents Canada in the race - with exciting results.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E12
programme.desc: In Naples, soccer isn't just a sport, it's a religion, and their fans are world renowned for their dedication, enthusiasm and creativity. David spends a Sunday with S.S.C. Napoli supporters, taking in the sights, sounds and foods (of course!) at Stadio San Paolo.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E3
programme.desc: Recently added to the world heritage list as a cultural asset, the iconic Mt. Fuji is a well-known symbol of Japan. Every year the volcano's scenic beauty draws more and more visitors from around the world. Dedicated mountain rangers, scientists, and eco-volunteers are working hard to preserve and protect the mountain from mankind while also protecting mankind from the mountain.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E7
programme.desc: Whilst renovating their garage, Steve and wife Marie never dreamt that they would find a World War Two bunker hidden underneath their garden. They decide to revolutionise the damp and dark space into a home office. Steve has devised an ingenious motorised lift that will lift the roof and let in light. Better still when the bunker is not in use the roof goes down and they keep full use of the garden and you'd never know what lies beneath.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E3
programme.desc: Wuzhong, home to the largest Muslim community on the silk road, and of course China's best place to enjoy Chinese halal food. Jamie will learn an unusual breakfast recipe that's certainly not for the faint-hearted and face his hardest noodle challenge yet. He also will uncover the secrets to the healthy yellow riverbank lifestyle that's helped shape the rich culinary history here an also got the younger generation rethinking their diets.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E4
programme.desc: Next stop, Dunhuang, the last city that trade merchants would pass through on the ancient silk road before braving the desert. Jamie will be introduced to the wonders of desert lifestyle to find out how the harsh local terrain has helped to^shape the unique food culture. It will definitely be a crazy ride by spending one day with a caravan of camels and, but all the pay is worth it. Jamie will cook in the VIP desert kitchen and attempt to make the hardest dish to date, for celebrating the unforgettable birthday party.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E5
programme.desc: What is it like to be stranded at Bangkok Airport? Darren from London has his passport stolen and British-Afghan veteran John is down to his last 20 pence till the tourist police step in. A panic attack grounds a young Aussie tourist in departures, a Swedish backpacker is savaged by a dog, and concern grows for the safety of a young Indian traveler.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E41
programme.desc: Ben and Rhys head to their third location on their Hobart Food Crawl to a small Italian style restaurant on the outskirts of the Hobart CBD. This restaurant is 20 seat and specialises in share plates, unique wines and communal dining. Up at The University of Queensland Ben and Joel make a traditional Italian dish, Cacio e Pepe, translating to ‘cheese and pepper', Joel explains a little about starches along the way.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E42
programme.desc: Rhys takes Ben down to Tom Mchugo's, an old style corner pub and hotel in the city, this will be their fourth stop on their food crawl. They kick back and enjoy a cold beer, oysters and what Rhys has announced is the best fried chicken in the south of Tassie.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E15
programme.desc: The village of Medhaghat in Assam- home to the Bodos, was soaked in festivities on Pablo's arrival. People dressed in vibrant clothes, environment filled with all sorts of food aromas, Medhaghat was a perfect destination for some gala time. Pablo fished, cooked and gorged on some exceptional food with the Bodos.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E14
programme.desc: Pablo explores more about Tiwas of Tharakunchi after learning that they are divided into two: The Tiwas of the Hills and Tiwas of the Plains. While he gets a chance to be among the Tiwas during the festivities Pablo is just blown away as he gets to know more about their food, cooking techniques, and their societal views.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E13
programme.desc: David meets his buddy Gianluca, who invites him to his families hometown of San Gregorio Armeno, a small town 90 minutes outside Naples. For five days straight, David, Gianluca and his family eat drink and celebrate family tradition, making tomato sauce, and hunting for truffles.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E1
programme.desc: Like the carnival festivals of Rio and Venice, Goa marks the days before Lent with an all-out celebration: three full days of eating, drinking, and partying. David takes part in all of the festivities, including an appearance on a float in Panjim's annual Carnival kick-off parade. He ends up spending time with some Italian expats and celebrating the holiday Venetian-style.

programme.title: Shark Nicole
programme.desc: The movement of the great white shark has remained an enigma. Join shark Nicole's world to explore the wonder, mystery & the danger.

programme.title: Wild Indochina
programme.desc: Indochina; three ancient kingdoms, Laos, Vietnam and Cambodia, linked by one great river: the mighty Mekong. A mystical land shaped by the forces of the monsoon. A region ravaged by war but, like a Phoenix, risen from the ashes. Within its boundaries can be found one tenth of the world's species, and some of the richest ecosystems on the planet. This is the land of the Mother River, one of the most bio diverse regions on Earth.

programme.title: Jungle Heroes E6
programme.desc: Wildlife SOS ended bear dancing in India, rescuing 628 bears from this cruel and illegal trade. Its medical team uses laser massage technology to help a bear that has had a brain haemorrhage, and a rapid response team also rushes to rescue an injured Nilgai - the largest and most dangerous antelope in India. A baby macaque monkey is also found abandoned in a cardboard box next to a highway.

programme.title: Secrets Of The Zoo S1E5
programme.desc: Baby fever spreads through the zoo, as a cheetah repopulation program goes into full effect, Takin Doc has a hitch in his getalong and the team must intervene, while Jack Hanna takes his grandkids on a whirlwind behind the scenes zoo tour and gives a speech to a crowd of zoo-goers, and the park's most chill residents get a frozen spaghetti seal treat.

programme.title: Legendary Catch E1
programme.desc: In this chapter of Carter Andrews' life long quest to find and catch the most legendary fish to swim on the planet, he is in hot pursuit of the giant White Sturgeon -- the apex predator in the rivers of the Pacific Northwest. Armed with years of angling knowledge, Carter teams up with different local experts along the way to find the mammoth fish he's after. Will Carter find the legendary fish that history proves have patrolled these rivers for years? Or will he be outwitted by this pre-historic species?

programme.title: Monster Fish S1E3
programme.desc: Follow Zeb Hogan as he dives with a giant freshwater stingray for the very first time and hand feeds this monster of the deep - its jaws have the power to crush bone. Zeb teams up with local expert Dr Nantarika Chansue and a commercial fishing guide to search central Thailand's rivers and estuaries for this critically endangered population.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S5E2
programme.desc: In this dramatic episode of Animal Fight Club, wildlife goes to war, from miniature murderers to the biggest brutes. Using under-the-skin CGI and compelling wildlife footage from some of the world's best documentary makers, we uncover the tactics and strategies behind the brawls. From African plains to the snow-covered wilds of North America, we reveal how nature's deadliest battles are fought over turf, dominance and the right to mate.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E2
programme.sub-title: The Tale Of The Cockatoo And The Kitty Cat
programme.desc: In this episode, we'll present you a cockatoo that enjoys giving massages to her once-feral feline friend, a California man who hangs ten with his surfing goat, and a hunting dog whose best friend and co-worker is a two-and-a-half-foot tall Eurasian eagle owl.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Compilations E2
programme.desc: The birds and the bees have never been so wild. Get ready for alien romance, bizarre reproduction and creative concepts in parenting.

programme.title: Jungle Heroes E6
programme.desc: Wildlife SOS ended bear dancing in India, rescuing 628 bears from this cruel and illegal trade. Its medical team uses laser massage technology to help a bear that has had a brain haemorrhage, and a rapid response team also rushes to rescue an injured Nilgai - the largest and most dangerous antelope in India. A baby macaque monkey is also found abandoned in a cardboard box next to a highway.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E5
programme.desc: Living Colors most demanding client is Jim Prappas, the head biologist at Rainforest Cafe. This time the project is at Disney World, the tanks that decorate this highly trafficked space are in desperate need of a reef makeover. As if a two week deadline wasn't difficult enough, Jim wants the restored reef to feature molds of the highly prized coral known as Stylophora pistillata.

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E1
programme.desc: We start on the tiny island of Batan, meeting a unique viper and a ubiquitous but also giant, land crab. Luzon is the main island of the Philippines. We drop in to Mindoro to see the most endangered large mammal in the Philippines, the tamaraw. The bustling capital of Manila dominates the centre of this large island but despite encroachments, huge areas of wilderness still exist. Here we meet blue tarantulas and strange forest birds. In the town of Pulilan we join a celebration that centres on the carabao, water buffalo. In the Verde Passage we join a group of photographers surveying the marine creatures of the area, from frog fish to pygmy seahorses. We also meet the people who have dedicated their lives to saving the most endangered crocodile in the world. On Palawan we find new sea creatures that charm and awe eco-tourists and take a trip along the longest navigable underground river to meet bats and swiftlets. We discover the sad recent history of the Palawan forest turtl.

programme.title: Dead By Dawn E1
programme.desc: At night, the dunes of the Arabian desert come to life with unique animals specially adapted to thrive in this hostile environment, from lizards that swim under the sand to spiders that can run ten miles per hour.

programme.title: Snake Island: Wild & Deadly
programme.desc: On a barren Australian island deadly tiger snakes survive in a place that is hostile and unforgiving. There is no fresh water or regular food. They live in the shadow of a brutal attacker that pecks their eyes out defending their offspring from the snake's ravenous hunger. Despite this they are thriving and have become giants of their kind. But why they are here and how they prosper in this desolate place has remained a mystery? until now.

programme.title: Monster Fish S1E4
programme.desc: The largest and oldest freshwater fish in North America, the white sturgeon is threatened with extinction; Zeb Hogan is on a mission to find out the reasons before it's too late. His first stop is the town of Castlegar in Canada, where he dives into the hazardous waters and looks for the giant creature.

programme.title: Wild Hawaii E2
programme.desc: Hawaii was born of fire into a world of water that has become as unique and spectacular as the islands themselves. This world for the most part remains hidden, secreted beneath the waves. Here creatures great and small struggle to live, while battling the lava, currents, and one another in an epic tale of survival.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E5
programme.desc: A young reindeer with many ailments needs Dr. Oakley's help to get back into fighting shape and an elderly porcupine poses a pokey problem.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E1
programme.desc: This episode of Unlikely Animal Friends features heartwarming stories of a two-legged chihuahua who befriends a silkie chicken, an adventurous mountaineer and his rock-climbing cat, and a goat who refuses to leave his beloved donkey's side. These stories profile the most unique, most surprising, and most loving animal friendships.

programme.title: China's Wild Side: Hidden Worlds
programme.desc: Tibet is dominated by the worlds largest plateau, buttressed by the great Himalayas and is the most inaccessible place on earth. Its creatures have adapted to survive at the top of the world. And Yunnan province is home to the greatest number of animal species in China. Each one must carve out a niche for itself. Diverse and spectacular, this is Chinas Wild Side.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E2
programme.desc: Trapped by the rising flood waters, Dikeledi must teach her wayward cubs the lessons of survival. But this brutal Kingdom is no place for a gentle cheetah family. The rotten clan of hyenas have taken control. There is one foe that will not lie down and tolerate their tyranny - the formidable Makulu Pack. These Wild Dogs have the cunning and experience, but with an ageing leader their strength soon starts to crumble from within and others are waiting to seize their opportunity.

programme.title: Legendary Catch E2
programme.desc: Carter is in the Bolivian jungle in pursuit of a mythical fish that's known for its strength and razor sharp teeth - The Golden Dorado. Pushing himself to the limit, Carter and a local native chief paddle dugout canoes and trek days up a secluded river to an ancient waterfall in the hopes of hooking one of these mystical fish. A formidable foe, Carter sees Dorado and can't hook them. When he can hook a Dorado it's not the legendary size he's after. With supplies running low for his journey, will Carter catch the Dorado he's after?

programme.title: Monster Fish S1E4
programme.desc: The largest and oldest freshwater fish in North America, the white sturgeon is threatened with extinction; Zeb Hogan is on a mission to find out the reasons before it's too late. His first stop is the town of Castlegar in Canada, where he dives into the hazardous waters and looks for the giant creature.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E1
programme.desc: To catch a deadly Black mamba, Simon must face his biggest fear - heights! And to save a spitting cobra, he deals with his OCD and digs in a poo pit!

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E2
programme.desc: Simon has a close call with a deadly black mamba in the middle of the night and finds his first ever Snouted cobra that's hitchhiked to Durban!

programme.title: Wild Hawaii E2
programme.desc: Hawaii was born of fire into a world of water that has become as unique and spectacular as the islands themselves. This world for the most part remains hidden, secreted beneath the waves. Here creatures great and small struggle to live, while battling the lava, currents, and one another in an epic tale of survival.

programme.title: The Real Black Panther
programme.desc: This isn't Wakanda. Deep in south India is a jungle kingdom that has inspired legends. Kabini, in the Nagarhole Tiger Reserve, is home to a rogue confederation of animal tribes all vying for territory, power and resources. Now a new king, Saya, is on the rise. He is the only black panther in this jungle. Lineage doesn't favor him, but he's got cunning and grit - and he plans to claim Kabini as his kingdom. From internal struggles for power to a cast reminiscent of 'The Jungle Book,' 'Rise of the Black Panther' transports you to the heart of this jungle kingdom. All hail the new king!

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E6
programme.desc: Dr. Oakley sees two stubborn muskoxen and a particularly wily coyote. A badly burned dog receives an innovative, if fishy, new treatment.

programme.title: Kingdom Of The White Wolf E1

programme.desc: Setelah seorang pengacara dijebak dan dijatuhi hukuman karena pembunuhan, ia mencoba menangkap pembunuh yang sebenarnya dari dalam penjara dengan bantuan seorang penipu.

programme.title: Parasite
programme.desc: Serangkaian kemalangan tak terduga menunggu saat keserakahan dan diskriminasi mengancam hubungan simbiosis yang baru terbentuk antara keluarga Park yang kaya dan keluarga Kim yang miskin.

programme.title: Detective K: Virtuous Widow
programme.desc: Detektif top Joseon menyelidiki serangkaian pembunuhan misterius yang berkaitan dengan konspirasi besar yang dapat menggemparkan seluruh negeri.

programme.title: The Chronicles Of Evil
programme.desc: Seorang detektif harus mengurai kesalahan di masa lalu untuk mencari tahu mengapa ia menjadi target utama dan menjadi pembunuh seorang sopir taksi.

programme.title: We Are Brothers
programme.desc: Dua kakak beradik yang terpisah sejak lahir bersatu kembali 30 tahun kemudian dan melakukan perjalanan untuk mencari ibu mereka yang menderita Alzheimer.

programme.title: Sunflower
programme.desc: Seorang mantan gangster yang dibebaskan dari penjara ingin menjalani kehidupan nan tenang bersama keluarganya. Namun, niatnya terancam saat seorang politisi mencoba membongkar restoran keluarganya demi membangun mal.

programme.title: Sori: Voice From The Heart
programme.desc: Saat mencari putrinya yang hilang, seorang ayah menemukan sebuah satelit yang mampu mengingat suara dari seluruh dunia. Menggunakan suara putrinya sebagai suar, satelit itu membantunya melacak sang putri.

programme.title: I Can Speak
programme.desc: Seorang nenek menjalin sebuah persahabatan nan unik dengan seorang pegawai negeri sipil. Untuk suatu alasan, ia meminta untuk diajari bahasa Inggris oleh PNS tersebut saat mengetahui bahwa ia mahir akan hal itu.

programme.title: Sunset In My Hometown
programme.desc: Ketika seorang rapper yang kurang sukses kembali ke kampung halamannya untuk mengunjungi ayahnya yang sakit, ia bertemu kembali dengan teman-teman dan keluarganya yang ia tinggalkan dulu.

programme.title: A Special Lady
programme.desc: Kisah tentang seorang wanita yang menjadi wakil ketua sebuah organisasi gangster terkemuka, melawan kekejaman para pria demi melindungi putra semata wayangnya.

programme.title: Typhoon
programme.desc: Seorang pemberontak dari Korea Utara mengungsi ke Korea Selatan, namun ia ditolak oleh pihak berwenang. Ia memutuskan untuk membalas dendam yang bisa mengakibatkan banyak kematian di kedua Korea.

programme.title: Part-Time Spy
programme.desc: Seorang mantan pekerja kontrak di Badan Keamanan Nasional bergabung dengan seorang detektif yang tengah menyamar untuk mendapatkan kembali uang yang dicuri dari bosnya lewat skema penipuan.

programme.title: Love, Lies
programme.desc: Seorang wanita penghibur diliputi kecemburuan setelah temannya sukses menjadi penyanyi pop dan kekasihnya jatuh hati padanya. Merasa dikhianati, ia mencoba mendapatkan kembali hal-hal yang hilang darinya.

programme.title: The Magician
programme.desc: Seorang pesulap muda nan berbakat jatuh cinta pada seorang putri yang bertunangan dengan mantan gurunya. Hal ini menyebabkan sebuah pertikaian sengit antara dua pesulap nan hebat.

programme.title: Dark Figure Of Crime
programme.desc: Terinspirasi dari kisah nyata, film ini menceritakan tentang sebuah pertarungan psikologis nan sengit antara seorang detektif polisi dan seorang pembunuh yang mengaku telah melakukan beberapa pembunuhan.

programme.title: Sori: Voice From The Heart
programme.desc: Saat mencari putrinya yang hilang, seorang ayah menemukan sebuah satelit yang mampu mengingat suara dari seluruh dunia. Menggunakan suara putrinya sebagai suar, satelit itu membantunya melacak sang putri.

programme.title: Chronicle Of A Blood Merchant
programme.desc: Sebuah kisah yang diangkat dari novel terkenal 'Chronicle of a Blood Merchant' karya YU Hua. Berlatar tahun 1960-an setelah Perang Korea, tentang seorang pria miskin dan kisah perjuangan hidupnya berserta keluarganya.

programme.title: The Classified File
programme.desc: Seorang detektif veteran dan sesosok peramal menjalin kerja sama yang tidak biasa untuk menyelamatkan seorang anak yang diculik sebelum terlambat.

programme.title: The Outlaws
programme.desc: Untuk menjaga perdamaian, seorang detektif nan kejam dan timnya berencana untuk meringkus gangster yang paling ditakuti di Seoul.

programme.desc: Selama pendudukan Jepang di tahun 1940-an, dua pria bekerjasama secara diam-diam membuat kamus bahasa Korea ketika bahasa tersebut dilarang.

programme.title: Tazza: The High Rollers
programme.desc: Setelah kehilangan seluruh tabungannya dalam permainan kartu ilegal, Goni menemukan bahwa hal itu sudah diatur dan berencana untuk mendapatkan uangnya kembali dengan bantuan penjudi veteran Tn. Pyeong.
